  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Anchor of Hope Charities has been working in Zambia since 2007 implementing health and education programs for underprivileged and orphaned children by providing K-12 education through a holistic approach. Rise Against Hunger meals are used in school feeding programs in regions of Nkoloma, Chisamba, Chainda, Roma, Katemwa and Choma. Anchor of Hope&#x2019;s approach is to move beyond the delivering of educational instruction and address the basic needs of children such as clean water, sanitation, food, clothing and healthcare. This strategy aims to provide children with improved nutrition and health care, reducing childhood illnesses, school absenteeism and greatly improving the likelihood of children successfully completing their education curriculum.</narrative>
  </description>
